4 SYNOPSIS:
5 This bill would propose an amendment to the
6 Constitution of Alabama of 2022, relating to Tuscaloosa
7 County, to authorize the full-time mayors of
8 municipalities in the county to participate in the
9 Employees' Retirement System of Alabama under the same
10 terms and conditions as other employees in the same
11 retirement system.
12
13
14 A BILL
15 TO BE ENTITLED
16 AN ACT
17
18 To propose an amendment to the Constitution of Alabama
19 of 2022, relating to Tuscaloosa County, to authorize the
20 mayors of municipalities in the county to participate in the
21 Employees' Retirement System of Alabama under the same terms
22 and conditions as other employees in the same retirement
23 system.
24 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
25 Section 1. The following amendment to the Constitution
26 of Alabama of 2022, is proposed:
27 PROPOSED AMENDMENT
28 In Tuscaloosa County, full-time mayors of
Page 1

In Tuscaloosa County, full-time mayors of
HB92 INTRODUCED
29 municipalities in the county may participate in the Employees'
30 Retirement System of Alabama under the same terms and
31 conditions as other employees in the same retirement system.
32 Any mayor holding office at the time of the ratification of
33 this amendment shall be eligible to purchase service credit in
34 the Employees' Retirement System for the time the official has
35 served in the current office. No individual may participate in
36 both a supernumerary program and the Employees' Retirement
37 System based on the same service.
38 Upon ratification of this constitutional amendment, the
39 Code Commissioner shall number and place this amendment as
40 appropriate in the constitution omitting this instructional
41 paragraph and may make the following nonsubstantive revisions:
42 change capitalization, hierarchy, spelling, and punctuation
43 for purposes of style and uniformity; correct manifest
44 grammatical, clerical, and typographical errors; revise
45 internal or external citations and cross-references; harmonize
46 language; and translate effective dates.
47 END PROPOSED AMENDMENT
48 Section 2. An election upon the proposed amendment
49 shall be held in accordance with Sections 284, 284.01, and 285
50 of the Constitution of Alabama of 2022, and the election laws
51 of this state. The appropriate election official shall assign
52 a ballot number for the proposed constitutional amendment on
53 the election ballot and shall set forth the following
54 description of the substance or subject matter of the proposed
55 constitutional amendment:
56 "Relating to Tuscaloosa County, proposing an amendment
Page 2

"Relating to Tuscaloosa County, proposing an amendment
